That Nisus wrote comese and asuese (i. e. apparently comedisse and assuevisse, for the words are corrupt) with one s, giving two reasons for so doing; (1) because a consonant cannot be doubled after a long vowel; (2) because the ‘antiqui’ did not double a consonant at all, but in- stead of doubling placed a mark over the single consonant. 2.
